    <briefdescription>
<para>The class <computeroutput><ref refid="structCGAL_1_1Surface__mesh__simplification_1_1Edge__collapse__visitor__base" kindref="compound">Surface_mesh_simplification::Edge_collapse_visitor_base</ref></computeroutput> provides a base class for models of the <computeroutput><ref refid="classEdgeCollapseSimplificationVisitor" kindref="compound">EdgeCollapseSimplificationVisitor</ref></computeroutput> concept. </para>    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para>This base class implements all of the visitor&apos;s callbacks. This way, users need only override the callbacks they are interested in. The callbacks <emphasis>are not virtual</emphasis> because this is not a dynamically polymorphic base class and the derived visitor will never be used polymorphically at runtime (is perfectly fine to override and hide a non-virtual method in the context of the static polymorphism used in the simplification algorithm).</para><para><parameterlist kind="templateparam"><parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>TriangleMesh</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
